summary: I've got some stuff to say about phil's new subscription service. While I know a lot of you are going to say 'I don't care what...
body:
I’ve got some stuff to say about phil’s new subscription service. While I know a lot of you are going to say ‘I don’t care what the content is! I would have paid even if it was nothing extra just to support phil!’ I need to just say….it’s wrong for phil to abuse that trust and that willingness to support him. Phil is a millionaire. He lives in a penthouse in central london. He has millions of adoring, young, impressionable fans. Being as successful as he is, that comes with a responsibility.

Phil doesn’t /need/ the money. Or rather, he wouldn’t need the money if he was making consistent content. Which is literally his job. Even without consistent content, he still has merch, two books, two tours….he is a millionaire. He doesn’t need to ask people to donate money to him in order for him to do his job.

This entire ordeal creates a hierarchy within the phandom. The ONE thing dan and phil have always stood behind is that they’ll never make content behind a paywall. Sure, there was extra stuff. Books, the tour, merch. But it was always EXTRA, it was never the same as their online content, their way of connecting and communicating with their fans. Putting up a wall between those with money and those without, and then having the audacity to give those who can afford it a discount on other things like merch? That goes against everything dan and Phil have ever claimed they stand for.

Think about it this way. If Jake Paul got on YouTube and told his fans he was making a subscription service where all you get is emojis, a discount in his merch store (where he will still make a big profit), and getting to ask him some questions for arguably the easiest content option on the platform - we would all scoff. We would all be pissed. We would say he’s abusing the love of his fans.

Phil has pulled a major dick move here. I have been subscribed to him since 2008, but today is the day, I unsubscribed from AmazingPhil. And if Dan does the same fucking thing, I’ll be doing the same. This is ridiculous. You all deserve better, and the fact that you don’t all believe that you deserve better is influencer marketing at it’s worst.

summary: Unpopular opinion apparently but it’s absolutely morally wrong to leak anything from Phil’s youtube membership stuff Like......
body:
Unpopular opinion apparently but it’s absolutely morally wrong to leak anything from Phil’s youtube membership stuff

Like… just don’t? Please? That’s like going to some artist/creator’s patreon and going “I’m going to share all of the patron exclusive posts because I don’t want the people who can’t afford it to be left out! :)” which completely defeats most of the reasons to even become a patron. 

Just, please consider this fact? I currently can’t afford to pay for the Phil’s membership stuff but I’m going to RESPECT the fact that he’s going to have member exclusive content. The same with the dozens of creators who I’d love to support but at this point in time I simply can’t afford to. I didn’t do it when I was a kid, and I don’t do it now. 

Just please

Respect Phil.
